Score and slice the fat on the @pork belly{700%g} into criss-crosses and season with 
@salt{1/4%tsp}. Lay the pieces in a cold #frying pan{} fat side down, turn the heat 
to medium-high and cook for ~{10-15%minutes}.

> The more you score the fat, the quicker the fat will 'render' (that's a cheffie term 
> for melting the fat!).

Boil a large #pot{} of water on medium-high heat with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Peel the 
@potatoes{4} and cut into 2cm cubes. Cook in the boiling water for ~{10-15%minutes} 
until cooked through, then drain and mash. Stir in @milk{1/2%cup}, 
@?butter{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a few grinds of @ground black pepper{}.

== Quick Pork Option ==

Heat the oven to 200 degrees. Transfer the pork belly from the frying pan to a 
#baking tray{}, fat side up (keep the frying pan with the pork belly fat as we'll 
use it later for the sauce). Mix @honey{1%tbsp} and @wholegrain mustard{1%tbsp} 
and rub all over the scored fat. Put them into the oven for ~{20%minutes} then remove 
and allow to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

== Slower Pork Option ==

If you have time, take the slower pork option by heating your oven to 180 degrees. 
Transfer the pork belly from the frying pan to a baking tray{}, fat side up (keep 
the frying pan with the pork belly fat as we'll use it later for the sauce). Mix 
@honey{2%tbsp} and @wholegrain mustard{1%2%tbsp} and rub all over the scored fat. 
Put them into the oven for ~{45-60%minutes} then remove and allow to rest for at 
least ~{5%minutes}.

== Sauce ==

Put the pan you used for the pork back on medium heat. Once the fat in the pan 
melts, add the @flour{1%tbsp} and stir to scrape off any bits from the pan. Dissolve 
the @chicken stock pot{1} in @water{300%ml} and gradually add to the pan giving it 
all a good stir.

Bubble this sauce over a medium heat until it has reduced by half. Add the remaining 
@honey{1%tbsp} and @wholegrain mustard{1/2%tbsp} and taste for seasoning and add more 
salt or pepper as you like.

> Add the juices that have leaked out of the rested meat for an extra hit of flavour.

== Beans ==

While the sauce is reducing, boil another pot of water with @salt{1/4%tsp} (or use 
the pot from the potatoes). Cut and discard the ends from the @green beans{2}. Cook 
in the boiling water for ~{3-4%minutes} or until 'al dente'.

> 'Al dente' simply means they have a little bit of crunch left in the middle.

== To Serve ==

Slice the pork belly into 1cm slices. Divide the mash and beans between your plates, 
top with slices of the pork belly and drizzle over the sauce.